The recommended way to add your custom asserter logic to Botium is by adding your own asserter module to Botium. You can find the details [here](https://botium.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/BOTIUM/pages/24477705/Developing+Custom+Asserters), but in short:

1. Create a file _MyCustomAsserter.js_:

```
module.exports = class CustomAsserter {
  constructor (context, caps, globalArgs) {
    this.context = context
    this.caps = caps
    this.globalArgs = globalArgs
  }
  assertConvoStep ({convo, convoStep, args, isGlobal, botMsg}) {
    if (botMsg.message !== &#39;hugo&#39;) throw new Error(&#39;expected hugo&#39;)
    return Promise.resolve()
  }
}
```

2. Register it in _botium.json_

```
{
  &quot;botium&quot;: {
    &quot;Capabilities&quot;: {
      ...
      &quot;ASSERTERS&quot;: [
        {
          &quot;ref&quot;: &quot;MY-ASSERTER-NAME&quot;,
          &quot;src&quot;: &quot;./MyCustomAsserter.js&quot;,
          &quot;global&quot;: false,
          &quot;args&quot;: {
            &quot;my-arg-1&quot;: &quot;something&quot;
          }
        }
      ]
    }
  }
}

```

3. Use this asserter in your convo files:

```
my-test-case

#me
hi

#bot
hi
MY-ASSERTER-NAME some-arg1|some-arg2

```

